<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTERS AND COOLER - OIL FILTERS AND
        HEADER - INSPECTION AND REPAIR
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSPECTION AND REPAIR</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Oil Filter Header</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect header for blocked orifices or damaged threads at oil filter threaded
                    inserts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove any debris which may be blocking the oil flow passages.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If thread damage is apparent, replace header.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Oil Filter Bypass Valve</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect the bypass valve for debris or scoring which could cause the valve to
                    stick open. Replace as required.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Bypass valve inspection is especially important any time an engine failure is experienced.
                            If the valve sticks in the open position, unfiltered oil will go directly to the crankshaft
                            and other vital engine parts.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect the bypass valve spring for wear.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Oil Filter</title>
            <para>A new larger capacity lubricating oil filter is available for service. This new filter is designated
                as an "EXTENDER&#8482;" oil filter and is constructed of a special paper media and additional media
                capacity to retain contaminants.
            </para>
            <para>The larger capacity "EXTENDERt" oil filter requires an additional one (1) quart of oil added to the
                lubrication oil system to compensate for the increased dimensions of the oil filter.
            </para>
            <para>The major feature of the new "EXTENDER&#8482;" oil filter provides for an extended time interval
                between changes of oil, fuel and coolant filters.
            </para>
